Linear search just checks every item one by one — simple, but slow on large data. Binary search keeps cutting the data in half each time, so it's way faster, but it only works if the data is sorted first.

For an e-commerce platform with thousands or millions of products, binary search is the better fit — it's much faster at scale, and sorting is usually a one-time cost handled by database indexing anyway. Linear search is fine only for small, unsorted lists.